subject: HR Update - Change in the PF Law
body: HR Update - Change in the PF Law Dear Synechronites, Due to a recent change in the Provident Fund (PF) law by the Supreme Court, the PF deduction will be applicable to all India full-time employees on a minimum basic salary of Rs. 15,000 per month, effective from Monday, April 1, 2019. This change is applicable to all India full-time employees whose minimum basic salary was less than or equal to Rs. 15,000/- per month. Your salary structure will be modified to accommodate this change and your basic salary will be updated to Rs.15,100 per month to comply with the PF law. Please note that this change may have an impact on your take-home salary and increase your PF contribution. Regards Team HR In case of any queries, please write to us at HR@Synechron.com
